{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1d573845-bdaf-4b72-891d-948bdb367243","content":"**Yes, you will hit a compatibility issue.** MSTest v4 (4.x) requires **.NET 8.0 or later** — it dropped support for `net6.0` (and `net7.0`). Since your project targets `net6.0`, upgrading the `MSTest` package to 4.x will fail to restore or compile.\n\nYour options:\n\n1. **Retarget to `net8.0`** (or later), then upgrade to MSTest v4.\n2. **Stay on MSTest 3.x** if you need to remain on `net6.0`.\n\nNote that .NET 6 reached end-of-support in **November 2024**, so upgrading to `net8.0` (LTS) is recommended regardless.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9c7febdf-9586-44c8-bf2e-ad031c918ad5","outputTokens":182},"id":"91034961-cbe5-40d3-b9fb-1c5bcef5beb6","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:01:07.071Z","parentId":"208e4186-ca9b-4d45-bd59-f1a3d1418029"}
